com.infantium.android.sdk

Class Element

  • Object
    • Element

  • public class Element
extends Object
    Compacts the different attributes of a Screen Element to be further referenced in the rest of the SDK
    Version:
    1.1.1.0, 30/10/2013
    See Also:
    Infantium_SDK.addElement(Element), Infantium_SDK.addElements(List)

    • Method Detail

      • setId

        public void setId(String id)
        Set the ID of the element. Each unique element should have a unique id in all the App. If the same element appears in different parts of the App it will have the same id (thus we can determine if the kid has seen the element before).
        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the element.

      • setType

        public void setType(ArrayList<String> type)
        Set the type of the element.

        The first position is reserved for the field Type and can be STATIC_OBJECT or ANIMATED_OBJECT.

        The second position is reserved for the field SubType and can be PHOTO_OBJECT, DRAW_OBJECT, PICTURE_OBJECT.

        Parameters:
        type - The list with the element type and subtype.

      • setDimension

        public void setDimension(String dimension)
        Set the dimension. Can be: 2D, 2.5D or 3D.
        Parameters:
        dimension - The element dimension.

      • setCategory

        public void setCategory(String category)
        Set the category of the element. The categories are: Polygon, Animal, Person, Object, Puzzle, BodyPart, Presence, Plant, Drawing, Text, Maths, MusicalInstrument, Vehicle
        Parameters:
        category - The element category

      • setSubcategory

        public void setSubcategory(String subcategory)
        Set the subcategory of the element. The subcategories are:

        For Polygons: Square, Circle, Rhombus, Pentagon, Star, Freeshape, Noshape.

        For Animals: Bear, Cat, Chicken, Cow, Crab, Dog, Goat, Goose, Horse, Mouse, Owl, Pig, Fish, Hedgehog, Rabbit, Lion, Tiger, Dolphin, Crow, Bird, Sheep, Skunk, Squirrel, Turkey, Wolf.

        For Persons: Adult, Child, Baby.

        For Objects: Toy, Card, Case, Other.

        For Puzzle: Top, Top_left, Top_right, Left, Right, Bottom, Bottom_left, Bottom_right, Center.

        For BodyPart: Arm, Body, Head, Eyes, Mouth, Ear, Leg, Hair, Nose, Tail.

        For Plant: Flower, Tree.

        For Drawing: Draw, Color.

        For Text: Long_text, A, B, C, ... X, Y, Z.

        For Maths: Plus, Minus, Equal, 1, 2, 3, ... up to the represented number.

        For MusicalInstrument: Guitar, Flute, Drum, Violin.

        For Vehicle: Ship, Plane, Car, Bus.

        Parameters:
        subcategory - The element subcategory

      • setPos

        public void setPos(ArrayList<Integer> pos)
        Set the element's position. The coordinates are: [ x(Required) , y(Required) , z(Optional ]
        Parameters:
        pos - The element position.

      • setVisibility

        public void setVisibility(float visibility)
        Set the visibility of the element. Visibility must be a float between 0.0 and 1.0.
        Parameters:
        visibility - The element visibility.

      • setAlpha

        public void setAlpha(float alpha)
        Set the transparency of the element. Alpha must be a float between 0.0 and 1.0.
        Parameters:
        alpha - Defaults to 1.0, means 100% opacity (% of opacity, from 0.0 to 1.0).
